      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Ugliest American</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Joseph and Wendy Ronghi letter on Steven Erlanger's April 2 article says their family will continue to stand behind US Army Sergeant Frank J Ronghi, accused of sexually assaulting and murdering Serbian girl, Merita Shabiu</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Steven Erlanger's article (April 2) on Frank J. Ronghi hit our family hard. The Frank we know is loving and good.</p>
        <p>Frank gave 12 years to serve our country. He went willingly and proudly to wherever the service sent him. We cannot begin to comprehend what is expected of our soldiers.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Steven Erlanger's article (April 2) on Frank J. Ronghi hit our family hard. The Frank we know is loving and good.</p>
        <p>Frank gave 12 years to serve our country. He went willingly and proudly to wherever the service sent him. We cannot begin to comprehend what is expected of our soldiers.</p>
        <p>Not a day passes that we as a family do not think of Merita Shabiu and her family. We pray that her family and ours will find answers. We also pray that someday they can find peace.</p>
        <p>We will continue to stand by Frank, and we will continue to love him no matter what the outcome.</p>
        <p>Joseph W. Ronghi</p>
        <p>Wendy Ronghi</p>
        <p>Lordstown, Ohio</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
